Operatives of the Lagos Rapid Response Squad (RRS), led by its Commander, Olayinka Egbeyemi, a Chief Superintendent (CSP) have arrested Treasurer of the Lagos State Council of the National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW), Alhaji Mustapha Adekunle (aka Sego) and Lagos Island ‘B’ Branch Chairman Alhaji Abdulazeez Adekunle Lawal (aka Kunle Poly) over the Thursday clash between the factional union members in Idumota, Lagos Island. RRS said the duo was the two principal suspects in the constant clashes in Idumota and its environs which have intermittently crippled commercial activities in the area. “The arrest was effected today at a meeting where the two NURTW members along with some other stakeholders converged. Read Also: Fans rejoice as MC Oluomo reconciles Iyabo Ojo, Faithia Balogun   UK scraps COVID-19 tests for fully vaccinated travellers…     Hanifa: Kano govt. revokes operational licences of all…     Court remands three for alleged murder of 5-year- old Hanifa   “The latest clash which occurred last week Thursday reportedly led to the death of a victim while commercial activities were paralysed in the area for some time until a joint team of police officers were deployed immediately to the area to restore peace,” RRS said. - Advertisement - The operatives said Kunle Poly and Sego have been transferred to Zone II, Onikan. NURTW Lagos State Council Chairman Alhaji Musiliu Akinsanya (aka MC Oluomo) described the action as a welcome development in resolving the crisis. “We need to allow the police to do their job without intervening in it. Their investigation would unravel the truth behind the intermittent clashes and bring it to an end,” Akinsanya said. Akinsanya urged union members to go about their lawful activities in peace, warning that anyone found causing crisis would face the law.